-- Buffon Saves Three in Penalty Shootout As Italy Defeats Uruguay
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 2013-06-30T18:57:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-30/buffon-saves-three-in-penalty-shootout-as-italy-defeats-uruguay.html
Gianluigi Buffon  saved three times
in the penalty shootout to help Italy beat Uruguay for third
place in the Confederations Cup in Brazil.  The match ended 2-2 after two periods of extra time. Italy
took the lead twice, only to have Uruguay come back with goals
from Edinson Cavani. Davide Astori scored in the 25th minute,
and then Cavani tied the match in the 58th minute. Alessandro
Diamanti again put Italy ahead in the 73rd minute, only for
Cavani to even it at 2-2, how it stayed until the match went to
penalty kicks.  Italian midfielder Riccardo Montolivo was sent off in extra
time for a second yellow card. Italy won the penalty shootout
3-2 as Buffon saved the kicks of  Diego Forlan , Martin Caceres
and Walter Gargano.  Host Brazil and world and European champion Spain meet
tonight in the final of the tournament, a warmup for next yearâ€™s
